The paper proposes a modification to Capsule Networks, a type of neural network architecture that has been primarily used in computer vision tasks. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a likely category. The paper also discusses the use of normalization techniques to improve the performance of Capsule Networks, which falls under the scope of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on several datasets, which suggests that it could be relevant to the fields of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques, such as Softmax and routing coefficients, which could also make it relevant to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
